The paper discusses the use of a statistical language model to predict pagination break points based on the semantic content of an article. This suggests a focus on natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), which are both covered by the cs.CL and cs.IR sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions comparing different approaches, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
